<body>
    <h1> Tables in HTML (Used to Represent Data in Tabular Form) </h1>
    <h3> Tables have 3 main tags: </h3>
    <ul>
        <li> <code>&lt;tr&gt; </code> - Table Row Tag  </li>
          <ul>
            <li> Used to display data in rows. </li>
          </ul>
        <li> <code>&lt;th&gt; </code> - Table Header Tag </li>
          <ul>
            <li> Used to define header cells in a table. </li>
          </ul>
        <li> <code>&lt;td&gt; </code> - Table Data Tag </li>
          <ul>
            <li> Used to enter actual data in table rows under headers. </li>
          </ul>
    </ul>

    <p>Below is a sample table showing student data using these tags:</p>

    <table>
        <caption> Students Data </caption>
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>ID</th>
            <th>Class</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Justin </td>
            <td> 1664 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Alizay </td>
            <td> 1665 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Albert </td>
            <td> 1666 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Aleena </td>
            <td> 1667 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <br/>

    <table>
        <tr>
            <th colspan = "3">
            <!-- Colspan is used when we want to show mutal info on all the columns. -->
                Student Information
            </th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Justin </td>
            <td> 1664 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Aleena </td>
            <td> 1667 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Albert </td>
            <td> 1666 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Alizay </td>
            <td> 1665 </td>
            <td> 12 </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
